9. List anti-patterns

Let me create the output directory first, then write DESIGN.md.


I'm establishing the theme as "Soft Nursery" with a calming aesthetic inspired by a cozy, sunlit room. The design uses cool-warm pastels anchored by lavender and blush rose accents, creating a serene, non-clinical feel. I'll use Nunito for both display and body typography to maintain that rounded, friendly character throughout the interface.

For the color palette, I'm working with soft violet (#A78BFA) as the primary brand color, light lavender tints for backgrounds, and a warm blush rose (#F9A8D4) for secondary accents. The typography relies on Nunito's rounded forms to reinforce the approachable, calming nature of the design system.

Now I'm establishing the dark theme variant, shifting to deeper violet tones (#7C3AED) as the primary with a muted background (#1F2937) and soft surface colors that maintain readability while keeping that gentle, nurturing quality even in low-light environments. I'm laying out the typography system with Nunito as the font, defining a clear hierarchy from hero display text at 57pt down to caption text at 11pt, each with specific weight and usage guidelines. The scale uses both display and body variants of Nunito to establish visual distinction between headings and body copy. For cards specifically, I'm setting 12pt corner radius with soft diffused shadows and a light lavender-white background, using 16pt internal padding with a subtle scale-down on press interaction. Buttons follow a rounded style with a 12pt corner radius to maintain the soft aesthetic, maintaining the 48pt minimum height for touch targets. Text inputs use a filled style with the same 12pt corner radius, light lavender background that shifts to deeper lavender on focus, and smooth label animation. Chips and bottom sheets share the 8pt corner radius language for consistency, with chips featuring a 24pt minimum height and bottom sheets capping at 90% screen height with a 40-point wide handle bar.

Navigation uses a bottom tab bar with a light surface background and soft violet indicator, supporting both outlined and filled icon states with label visibility. The app bar itself is transparent to the surface color with title text in subtitle style, remaining fixed during scroll interactions. Layout spacing follows an 8-point base unit with 16pt horizontal screen padding and 24pt vertical section gaps, maintaining consistent rhythm across the interface. Screen horizontal padding is 16pt, section vertical spacing is 24pt, card gap is 12pt, list item minimum height is 56pt, minimum touch target is 48pt, bottom sheet handle bar is 40pt wide and 4pt tall, and safe areas must be respected for both the status bar and home indicator.

Animations follow a gentle approach: page transitions use 300ms smooth deceleration for content sliding and fading, micro-interactions like button presses and chip selections are 200ms with snappy ease-out, hero transitions for shared elements are 350ms with a fast-out-slow-in curve, staggered list items appear with 50ms delay between each, bottom sheets slide up over 250ms with smooth deceleration, and pull-to-refresh indicators snap in and out in 150ms.

I need to avoid certain design patterns: platform colors must come from the design system palette, text sizing must follow the type scale, spacing must use the defined tokens, elevation must be intentional and communicate hierarchy, Inter and Roboto are not allowed as defaults, gradients and neon accents should be avoided, shadows need purpose, desktop patterns like sidebars and hover tooltips don't belong in mobile, touch targets must be at least 48 points, critical actions should stay in the thumb zone, and pure black (#000000) should be replaced with off-black or deep charcoal.
